      "message": "on big-O:\n current impl. is\n   AddNoBlock: O(1) for blocking, O(batches) for dropOldest\n   Lease: O(log(batches))\n   NACK/ACK: O(batches)\n   \nAfter more thinking, why keep leased batches in the same heap instead of a separate data structure like a freelist?\n  AddNoBlock: O(1) for blocking, O(batches) for dropOldest\n  Lease: O(log(batches))\n  NACK/ACK: O(workers + log(batches))\n  \nNot sure if it\u0027s better or worse in the end. I\u0027m also willing to land this as is and iterate afterwards, because we are spending too much time on this :(",
