      "side": 1,
      "message": "conclusion from above stands, but I have another idea:\n\none could also argue that O(batches) should be O(workers) in practice, so we could simplify code substantially by keeping all batches in a slice and maintaining {minNextSend, oldestBatchIdx}:\n  AddNoBlock: O(1) for both\n  Lease: O(batches)      [updates minNextSend]\n  NACK:  O(batches)      [updates oldestBatchIdx, minNextSend]\n  ACK:   O(batches)      [updates oldestBatchIdx]\nand I think code becomes simpler to think about -- just iterations over the slice, no more complex h[0] and Less() ordering to keep in mind.",
